<br>
I'm not one to hide that fact that I'm semi-ignorant to the &quot;Uber&quot; game, but perhaps someone with a little more knowledge can shed some light on this for me. <br>
<br>
We have 3 upper level straight AC buffs, but for the sake of this thread I'm going to leave <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Transons Phantasmal Protection</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> out of this. <br>
<br>
Here are Lucy's interpretations of the spells we have.<br>
<br>
Spell: Phantom Armor: 2: Increase Hitpoints by 5 per tick, 4: Increase AC by 21 (L52) to 22 (L60), Mana: 225, Classes: MAG/52, Skill: Abjuration, Casting: 5, Recast: 0, Target: Self, Duration: 1 hour(s) 30.0 mins, Reagents: Cat's Eye Agate x 4, Source: Live - 07/31, <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://lucy.fnord.net/s/AAaC">lucy.fnord.net/s/AAaC</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> <br>
<br>
Spell: Phantasmal Armor: 2: Increase Hitpoints by 5 per tick, 4: Increase AC by 21 (L54) to 22 (L60), Mana: 225, Classes: MAG/54, Skill: Abjuration, Casting: 5, Recast: 0, Target: Self, Duration: 1 hour(s) 30.0 mins, Reagents: Pearl x 1, Source: Live - 07/31, <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://lucy.fnord.net/s/AAs">lucy.fnord.net/s/AAs</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<br>
Can someone please explain to me the benifit of owning Phantasmal Armor, let alone chasing it down in Ssra or shelling out hard earned plat for it? It takes the same amount of time, for the same amount of mana, for the exact same effect. It also takes a pearl at 5pp per, as opposed to 4 cat's eyes which is roughly 1/10th the cost. <br>
<br>
<br>
What I propose is something that looks more like this<br>
<br>
Spell: Phantasmal Armor: 2: Increase Hitpoints by 10 per tick, 4: Increase Mana by 1 per tick 8: Increase AC by 29 (L54) to 35 (L60), Mana: 250, Classes: MAG/54, Skill: Abjuration, Casting: 7, Recast: 0, Target: Self, Duration: 30.0 mins, Reagents: Pearl x 1<br>
<br>
This would not stack with TPP (I think I did the slots right) but would give us more HP regen to offset the 2mana/tick advantage. It would basically give us a choice of what we chose to regen while not throwing the balance out of whack by giving us both at the same time without the cost of a moderately expensive reagent and 1/3 the duration. Due to the relative rarity of <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Phantasmal Armor</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> because of it's drop rate, and single mob location I don't see how this change would upset anything as far a game balance goes. <br>
<br>
What do you guys think? <p>[56 Conjurer] <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=64170" target=new>Allaa</a> (Dark Elf) < Amicus Primus >
